I"”0<img src="/assets/FLStudio/FLPianoDrums.png" alt="Drums">
<div class="image-caption">Drums in the Piano Roll</div>

<p>FLStudio‚Äôs manual has some bold claims in it‚Ä¶</p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">FL Studio's Piano roll has the well deserved reputation as the best Piano roll in the business.</code></p>

<p>And‚Ä¶</p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">FL Studio has, arguably, the most powerful Piano roll editor available. </code></p>

<p>If you‚Äôve read my website much then you know I really rev up when I see claims made about features. I‚Äôll be spending this post, and the following 2 posts discussing MIDI editing/entry which is mostly done in the Piano Roll.</p>

<p>To start with, I‚Äôm going to cover the bare basics of Piano Roll usage. Is it really the best?</p>

